title: Ian Dury - 13 albums, third try, should work this time
description:
So here is what I think is going on.. I am using utorrent, and I had the option checked to put a flag on incomplete files. But when the torrent started uploading, it was flagging my files as incomplete that were not. I have listened to them and they are fine. So it may be that some of what you have are complete files they just look like they&#039;re not.

Anyway, I removed that option, renamed all the times, and took out all the zune artwork hidden files that were getting in the way, and put back in the two albums I took out last time for the same problem and made a new torrent. So try the new one (maybe just picking the files that weren&#039;t working before) and we&#039;ll see how that goes.

I know this is frustrating, I&#039;m getting pretty frustrated too. Just keep me posted on what&#039;s happening on your end and we&#039;ll get this worked out.

For those of you just joining us, here is the list:


1. Apples
2. Reason to be Cheerful (2 disc)
3. Sex & Drugs & Rock & Roll
4. Do it Yourself (2 disc)
5. Handsome (Kilburn & the High Roads)
6. Stiffs Live (w/ Costello, Lowe, etc.)
7. Straight from the Desk
8. Bus Driver&#039;s Prayer
9. Live in Lucianatten, 1980 (bootleg)
10. Warts &#039;n&#039; Audience
11. New Boots and Panties (1 disc)
12. Lord Upminster
13. Live at Pinkpop 1981 (bootleg)
